== About ==
  Make Sense Signal Visualization Tools (SigVis) is a cross-platform graphical
  desktop application to assist developers and users of the Make Sense
  Platform/GRAIL Project in visualizing signal data from the system.  It
  focuses primarily on visualizing RSSI data from wireless transmitters and
  receivers in the system.

Version 1.0.0 - TBD
  + Initial version.
  + Visualizations available:
    - Bar Charts (RSSI/Variance)
    - Line Charts (RSS/Variance/Combo)
    - Voronoi Heat Map (RSSI/Variance) for specific devices or entire regions.
    - Heat Stripes (RSSI/Variance)
    - Intersection Map (RSSI/Variance)
    - Ambient Variance Map (Cloud simulation)
  + Save and restore cached data to disk.
  + Multiple windows with shared or separate data caches.
  + Linux (Bash) and Windows (Batch) start-up scripts.
